prompt:
Add a public delegate called MathOperation to Domain.calr that takes two i32 parameters and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor delegate definition syntax:
§DEL{d001:MathOperation:pub}
  §I{i32:a}
  §I{i32:b}
  §O{i32}
§/DEL{d001}

The §DEL{id:name:visibility} syntax defines a delegate type:
- id is a unique delegate identifier
- name is the delegate type name
- §I defines the parameter types
- §O defines the return type
- Delegates are function type signatures
